<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Privacy Policy</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/tailwindcss@2.2.19/dist/tailwind.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        .container-fluid {
            max-width: 1200px;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body class="bg-gray-100 font-sans">

    <div class="container-fluid mx-auto px-8 py-6">
        <a href="/"
            class="inline-block px-4 py-2 text-white font-semibold bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow-md hover:bg-gray-700 transition duration-300 ease-in-out mb-4">
            Go to Home Page
        </a>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800">Privacy Policy</h1>
    </div>


    <main class="container-fluid mx-auto p-8">
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-4">Introduction and Consent</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                Your privacy is paramount to us. This Privacy Policy governs the collection, use, and disclosure of your
                personal information when you use our website and services at [Your Website URL]. By registering for an
                account, enrolling in a course, or otherwise interacting with our platform, you signify your acceptance
                of this policy. If you do not agree with the terms, please refrain from using our services.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-4">Information We Collect</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">We collect and process the following types of information:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mb-6 space-y-2">
                <li><strong class="text-gray-800">Personal Identification Information:</strong> This includes data you
                    voluntarily submit, such as your full name, email address, phone number, and college name. This data
                    is essential for program enrollment and communication.</li>
                <li><strong class="text-gray-800">Payment Information:</strong> When you make a payment, we collect
                    transaction details, including the amount paid and transaction ID. We do not store your full credit
                    card or bank account details.</li>
                <li><strong class="text-gray-800">Technical and Usage Data:</strong> We automatically collect
                    non-personal data like your IP address, browser type, operating system, and a record of the pages
                    you visit. This helps us analyze user trends, improve our website's performance, and enhance
                    security.</li>
                <li><strong class="text-gray-800">Cookies and Tracking:</strong> We use cookies and similar technologies
                    to track activity on our service and hold certain information. You can instruct your browser to
                    refuse all cookies or to indicate when a cookie is being sent. However, if you do not accept
                    cookies, you may not be able to use some portions of our service.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-4">How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">The information we collect serves several key purposes:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mb-6 space-y-2">
                <li><strong class="text-gray-800">Service Provision:</strong> To process your registration, manage your
                    enrollment, and provide access to course content.</li>
                <li><strong class="text-gray-800">Communication:</strong> To send you program updates, payment
                    confirmations, and important announcements. We may also use your contact information to respond to
                    your inquiries and offer support.</li>
                <li><strong class="text-gray-800">Personalization:</strong> To tailor your learning experience by
                    recommending relevant courses or content based on your profile and interactions.</li>
                <li><strong class="text-gray-800">Analytics:</strong> To monitor and analyze website usage, which helps
                    us improve our platform's functionality and user interface.</li>
                <li><strong class="text-gray-800">Legal Compliance:</strong> To meet our legal obligations, including
                    responding to valid requests from law enforcement agencies or government authorities.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-4">Disclosure of Information to Third Parties</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                We do not sell, trade, or rent your Personal Information to third parties. We may, however, share data
                with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in operating our website, conducting our
                business, or serving our users, provided those parties agree to keep this information confidential. This
                may include payment processors or email service providers.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-4">Your Data Protection Rights</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                Depending on your location, you may have the right to access, update, or request the deletion of your
                personal data. If you wish to exercise these rights, please contact us at [Your Support Email].
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-4">Changes to this Policy</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
                We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy at any time. We will notify you of any changes by
                posting the new policy on this page and updating the "last updated" date at the top of the policy. You
                are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.
            </p>
        </div>
    </main>
</body>

</html>